President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Brian Deese as Deputy Director of the Office of Management and Budget. Deese has previously served in various economic policy roles, including as Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Director of the National Economic Council. He has also worked on the Obama-Biden Transition Team and the Obama for America Campaign. Deese's experience includes work on fiscal policy, international trade, and globalization. He holds a B.A. in Political Science from Middlebury College and a J.D. from Yale Law School. President Obama praised Deese's leadership and understanding of economic and budgetary policy, and expressed confidence that he will serve America well in this new role.